  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>There's a great choice at breakfast to get you started for the day. It's served to the table and includes options like croissants, cakes, yoghurt, fresh fruit, cereals, jams, honey, cheeses, local sausages and freshly baked bread. If you fancy a hot breakfast there's also scrambled eggs, boiled eggs, bacon, sausages and cooked tomatoes. To top it off there's freshly squeezed fruit juices and just ask the staff and they'll be happy to bring you freshly made hot drinks including <span>espresso, cappuccino, Americano, hot chocolate and tea. </span></p>
<p>Breakfast is from 7 - 10am on weekdays and 7 - 10.30am at weekends</p>
<p><strong>Bistrot Tower Restaurant</strong> is the hotel's main restaurant. In the evening they serve tasty regional and Italian dishes, as well as original combinations of international cuisine. If you're travelling with children, speak to your waiter, they'll be able to advise on the special kid's menu. </p>
<p>Dinner is available from 7 - 10pm Monday to Friday</p>
<p><strong>The Tower Hotel Bars </strong>are a nice place to grab a coffee after a day exploring bologna, or a quick drink before dinner. </p>
<p>The ground Floor Bar is open on Saturday and Sunday 5 - 10pm &amp; the first floor bar is open Monday to Friday 5 - 11pm.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
